Date:  0/0/1947
Source:  Native Animals of NZ
Author:  POWELL
Vol / Page:  67
Edition:
Quote:  Thirteen species of flat-fishes are known from New Zealand waters, including a large Turbot, <i>Colistium nudipinnis</i>, which is comparatively rare, and the Megrim, <i>Caulopsetta scapha</i> , which is not popular as a food fish as it is usually very thin.
Notes:

