Date:  0/0/1967
Source:  Animals of NZ, The
Author:  NATUSCH
Vol / Page:  217
Edition:
Quote:  All [flatfish] but the megrim (<i>Caulopsetta</i> ... ) have the right (as opposed to the left) side uppermost ... All are excellent food fish-again with the exception of the megrim, once dubbed `cadgers' - fish' because of its suitability for palming off on those who hover round landing fishing-craft in the hope of perks, especially flatfish. <i>Ibid.</i> 218 [Caption] Fig. 66: FLATFISHES. I. <i>Turbot.</i> 2. Brill;(<i>both </i>Colisteum <i>spp</i>). 3. Flounder, <i>Rhombosolea</i>. 4. Sole, <i>Peltorhamphus</i>. 5. Megrim or witch, <i>Caulopsetta</i> (eyes left!). 6. Lemon sole, <i>Pelotretis. </i>
Notes:

